OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FBut what is MenB, and how does it
OL,7,Fdiffer from other strains of
OL,8,Fmeningitis?
OL,10,FWhat is meningitis?
OL,12,FMeningitis is an infection of the
OL,13,Fprotective membranes that surround the
OL,14,Fbrain and spinal cord. It is usually
OL,15,Fcaused by a bacterial or viral
OL,16,Finfection. Bacterial meningitis is
OL,17,Frarer but more serious than viral
OL,18,Fmeningitis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
