OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773774689
OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FMeningitis can affect anyone, but it
OL,7,Fis more common in babies, children,
OL,8,Fteenagers, and young adults.
OL,10,FIt can be very serious if not treated
OL,11,Fquickly, and can lead to life-
OL,12,Fthreatening sepsis and permanent
OL,13,Fdamage to the brain or nerves.
OL,15,FWhat is MenB and how serious is it?
OL,17,FMenB is a type of bacterial meningitis.
OL,19,FIt is caused by the Neisseria
OL,20,Fmeningitidis bacteria, otherwise known
OL,21,Fas the meningococcus.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
