OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FDr Simon Clarke, associate professor
OL,7,Fof cellular microbiology at the
OL,8,FUniversity of Reading, said:
OL,9,F"Meningococcal bacteria come in
OL,10,Fseveral strains, known as serogroups,
OL,11,Fof which B and C are the most common
OL,12,Fcauses of disease in the UK."
OL,14,FOccasionally, these bacteria break
OL,15,Fthrough the lining at the back of the
OL,16,Fthroat and can pass into the
OL,17,Fbloodstream, leading to infection.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
