PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773774689
OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FMenB can be extremely serious, as
OL,7,Fexperts estimate that up to one in
OL,8,Fevery 10 cases of bacterial meningitis
OL,9,Fis fatal.
OL,11,FMeningococcal bacteria can lead to the
OL,12,Fbrain's lining becoming inflamed,
OL,13,Fwhich can cause meningococcal
OL,14,Fsepticaemia, commonly known as sepsis.
OL,16,FThe disease can be treated with
OL,17,Fantibiotics if it is caught early,
OL,18,Fwhich can result in full recovery.
OL,20,FIs there a vaccine?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
