CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773774689
OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FSome groups of meningococcal disease
OL,7,Fcan be prevented by vaccines, of which
OL,8,Fthere are multiple available in the UK.
OL,10,FThe MenB jab offers protection against
OL,11,Fmeningococcal group B bacteria and is
OL,12,Frecommended for babies aged eight
OL,13,Fweeks, followed by a second dose at 12
OL,14,Fweeks and a booster at one year.
OL,16,FBut the majority of young people born
OL,17,Fbefore 2015 are not protected against
OL,18,Fmeningitis B unless they have had the
OL,19,Fjab privately, as it was introduced on
OL,20,Fthe NHS for babies in 2015.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773774689
OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FDr Clarke said: "MenB has historically
OL,7,Fbeen harder to vaccinate against than
OL,8,Fother strains because its outer
OL,9,Fsurface resembles human tissue, making
OL,10,Fit more difficult for the immune
OL,11,Fsystem to recognise as a threat."
OL,13,F"The MenB vaccine works by targeting
OL,14,Fspecific proteins on the bacterial
OL,15,Fsurface rather than the outer coating,
OL,16,Fwhich is how earlier meningococcal
OL,17,Fvaccines worked", he added.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
