CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773774689
OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FOther routine childhood jabs,
OL,7,Fincluding the 6-in-1 and pneumococcal
OL,8,Fvaccines, can protect against
OL,9,Fmeningitis.
OL,11,FElsewhere, the MenACWY vaccine is a
OL,12,Fsingle-dose jab that protects against
OL,13,Ffour strains of meningococcal
OL,14,Fbacteria. It was also introduced in
OL,15,F2015.
OL,17,FIt is offered to teenagers in school
OL,18,Fand is also available to those
OL,19,Fentering university, up to the age of
OL,20,F25.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
