OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773774689
OL,3,CWhat do we know about Meningitis B and
OL,4,Chow serious is it?
OL,6,FTreatments include antibiotics and
OL,7,Ffluids administered directly into a
OL,8,Fvein, oxygen if there are breathing
OL,9,Fdifficulties, and, in some cases,
OL,10,Fsteroid medication to prevent swelling
OL,11,Faround the brain.
OL,13,FPatients may need to stay in the
OL,14,Fhospital for a few days or weeks.
OL,16,FIn cases of mild meningitis, patients
OL,17,Fmay be sent home if tests confirm it
OL,18,Fis viral, which usually gets better on
OL,19,Fits own. Most patients start to feel
OL,20,Fbetter within seven to 10 days.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
